## Reaction arrow annotations

Use `indigo.MyReaction` for ChemDraw-style arrow labels:

```python
from indigo import MyReaction

rxn = MyReaction(
    smiles="c1ccccc1Br.CBr.[Na].[Na]>>Cc1ccccc1.[Na]Br.[Na]Br",
    catalyst=["Na", "Dry Ether"],
    temperature="150",
    pressure="20",
)
rxn.render("reaction_arrow_annotations.svg")
```

`temperature="150"` becomes `150°C`, and `pressure="20"` becomes `20 psi`.
